main event: Two witnesses observed two star-like objects in the sky near Nashville, Tennessee on 8 June 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 10 minutes,The first object moved southwest while the second was potentially a reflection of the moon,The objects were noted to be lower and west of the moon,One object disappeared and reappeared at approximately 1,200 feet,There was no physical evidence or photographs taken during the observation.
witness description: two individuals observing from a distance
